eZ Tags extension installation documentation

Requirements
============

    * eZ Publish 4.3+
    * eZ Find
    * eZ JSCore


Installation
============

 1. Unpack/unzip

    Unpack the downloaded zip package into the 'extension' directory of your
    eZ Publish installation.

 1. Create SQL tables in your eZ Publish database

    Extension requires two additional tables to be added to your database. Use the following command from your eZ Publish
    root folder, replacing "user", "password", "host" and "database" with correct values and removing double qoutes

    mysql -u "user" -p"password" -h"host" "database" < extension/eztags/sql/mysql/schema.sql

 2. Activate extension

    Activate the extension by using the admin interface ( Setup -> Extensions ) or by
    prepending eztags to ActiveExtensions[] in settings/override/site.ini.append.php:

    [ExtensionSettings]
    ActiveExtensions[]=eztags

    Be sure to place the eztags entry before ezwebin entry in active extension list if you wish to see demo content.

 3. Regenerate autoload array

    Check the eZ Publish docs for your version on how this is done.
    Or go to Setup -> Extensions and click on the button there.

 4. Clear caches

    Clear all caches (from admin 'Setup' tab or commandline).

 5. Speedup ajax calls

    1. Copy or symlink index_treemenu_tags.php from this extension to the root folder of eZ Publish (next to index.php)

    2. Add the following rewrite rule:

		* .htaccess
		 RewriteRule tags/treemenu/? index_treemenu_tags.php
		 RewriteRule ^index_treemenu_tags\.php - [L]

       * Virtual Host mode
		 RewriteRule tags/treemenu/ /index_treemenu_tags.php [L]

 6. Allow anonymous users access to tags

    For anonymous users to be able to see tags on your site, grant access to "view" function of "tags" module to Anonymous role